<font color="#FF0000">KEEP THE CAMPFIRES BURNING</font><br>
<tt>Wed Aug 20 19:06:07 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
One of the first things a fish discovers when he jumps out the water where he has lived all his life, is not the air that he did not know existed above, what he discovers is the water he has lived in all his life. <br><br>
So was it in Nam as Humming Eagle has related it is the honor we took into Nam that revealed how we would react. It is what our parents, teachers, our home environment, friends and others had shared with us that dictated what values we would take into battle. How we would respond under fire, what we could endure upon our return.<br><br>
&quot; You must love life, honor it, believe in it, to be able to take it from others in war. &quot;<br>
Cook Barela<br><br>

